Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt, the Holy Family are in the centre being offered fruit by John the Baptist at right, a large angel collects from the from the tree and above three putti occur in a cloud, after Titian. 1569 Engraving
Curator's comments: Long description of subject in ink on verso.
Associated names: Representation of: St John the Baptist (Prodromos)
Acquisition notes: The print is mis-stamped H,10.52 from a later positioning of the album which had been inventoried as H,4.
